Kerr Spacetime Geodesic Generator documentation (WIP)

DEPENDENCIES:

Build:
valac
libjson-glib-dev
libgsl0-dev

Run:
vpython
matplotlib
jq
bc
imagemagick
ffmpeg


Sample usage:

1.	Build all the Vala executables, and test them

./build-all [fast]

icdata=icgen-data
ic=initial-conditions
data=/tmp/data
pot=/tmp/potential

./run-tests 2>/dev/null
rm -f $ic; ./rg2 2>/dev/null


2.	Run and plot one of the initial conditions files:

ic=ic/Light1
jq . $ic; ./bh3d.rk4 <$ic | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic` &


3.	Create an initial conditions data file

echo '{ "rMin": 3.0, "rMax": 12.0, "thMin": 0.15, "spin": 1.0 }' >$icdata; jq . $icdata

echo '{ "rMin": 9.0, "rMax": 12.0, "thMin": 0.25, "spin": -1.0 }' >$icdata; jq . $icdata


4.	Generate initial conditions to stdout:

Spherical orbit:
echo '{ "r": 12.0, "thMin": 0.45, "spin": 1.0 }' | ./icgen 2>$pot | jq .

Non-spherical orbit:
echo '{ "rMin": 11.5, "rMax": 12.5, "thMin": 0.45, "spin": 1.0 }' | ./icgen 2>$pot | jq .


5.	Edit the inital conditions data and/or the inital conditions file and run again with symplectic integrator and tau or t as the time parameter:

vi $icdata; jq . $icdata
./icgen <$icdata >$ic 2>$pot; jq . $ic
vi $ic; jq . $ic

./bh3d <$ic | ./finterp.py tau 0.5 | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic`


6.	Some example initial conditions pipelines . . .

jq . $ic; ./bh3d.rk4 <$ic | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic` &
jq . $ic; nc.openbsd pi 1234 <$ic | ./plotBH.py `jq .M $ic` `jq .a $ic` &


7.	Generate geodesic data and pass it to David Madore's kerr-image raytracer (ftp://ftp.madore.org/pub/madore/misc/kerr-image.c).

./icgen <$icdata 2>$pot | ./bh3d.rk4 | ./raytrace-commands 0 2>/dev/null | ./raytrace


8.	Make a video out of the output files:

ffmpeg -y -i RaytracingOutput/%04d.png -c:v libx264 -crf 1 raytrace.mp4
mplayer raytrace.mp4 -fps 10


REFERENCE DATA

Particle trajectories

http://staff.science.nus.edu.sg/~phylyk/downloads/reports/sp2172_report.pdf

Light trajectories

http://www.physics.nus.edu.sg/~phyteoe/kerr/paper.pdf

